Module root for the `bwrap` argv builder; re-exports the actual logic from `build` and `config` submodules and documents the cage's mount layout, but contains no logic itself.

The doc comment is the authoritative reference for the mount plan and must stay in sync with `build.rs`'s implementation: target project bind-mounted RW at its real host path (not an alias — ADR-046, so paths inside/outside the cage match for build reproducibility), secret files masked with empty-file RO binds, toolchain dirs RO at identical host paths, `/cage/bin` as a tmpfs holding RO-bound host CTX tools plus `claude`, `/opt/cage/rules.md` RO, and `/run/ctx` RO exposing the API proxy socket as the only egress path (the cage has no network otherwise).

This module is pure — no I/O, no subprocess exec, no filesystem access — by design; that's enforced by convention across `build.rs` and `config.rs`, not by anything in this file. Callers construct a `BwrapConfig` elsewhere (in the lifecycle module, from CLI flags and environment) and pass it to `build_bwrap_args` to get the final `Vec<OsString>` for `Command::new("bwrap")`. The re-exported constants (`API_SOCK_NAME`, `CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CONFIG`, `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED`, `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR`) define the fixed in-cage paths referenced by the mount layout above and are likely depended on by other cage code that needs to locate these paths at runtime.